9:
What... time is it? Noon? Oh, I've got
that meeting...
22:
Why are you keeping your back
turned?
29:
Yes... He was. Pathetic and craven
from the very beginning.
32:
He made me stronger by showing
just how he weak he was—and by
pretending he never loved me...
35:
Mumbling to yourself about past
romances, now are we? DO go on!
40:
Don't you dare utter a word of this to
anyone else!
44:
You must pay for your
transgressions, humans.
48:
You've got some nerve, talking
about "transgressions"...
51:
You're nothing more than a
poorly-designed, miserable pile of
Overlord scrap!
55:
I could give a rat's rotten ass from
how "high on up" you came—you
DON'T get to talk down to humans
like that!
58:
O Light! O Darkness! O Free Will that
carves through shadow! Strike down
these foes!
65:
Now, then. I suppose it's time I
finished up some homework.
69: O Light that reveals all creation!
72:
O Darkness that lurks within all
creation! O Stars that dwell within
our souls!
87: I know... I made a huge mistake...
91:
When the Origin Dragon looked at
me , I... If only I hadn't run away! If
only... I hadn't hesitated...
94: If only I were more like you...
98:
Failure isn't something to be
ashamed of.
101:
After all, we've seen our fair share of
it. When we first met... When our
research was discovered... And
countless other times...
104:
The two of us have failed more often
than not, wouldn't you agree?
109:
Th-that's not true— 
...Wait. You might actually be right...
113:
But it's okay. You're an expert in
smoothing over mistakes, are you
not?
116:
You've gotten this far... What's a few
more messes to clean up? And a
few more after that.
120:
I suppose that's true... Then,
Nihilyana...
129:
It's good to see you safe and sound...
When I heard you were injured, I...
Well, I...
133:
Ohhh, right. You're that Guild Knight...
Let me think... Alex, was it?
136:
Actually, it's Verdias! But I'm so
overjoyed to see you're okay!
137:
Just thinking I might have lost you
made me realize... You're all I have!
140:
Ah, right. Now it's all coming back to
me. Verdias, yes. Do we really have
to do this now?
143:
I swear on my blade that I shall
protect you, no matter the—
146:
Spare me the sentimentality, you
blasted dolt! Get out there and help
the townspeople, or I swear I'll fry
what little brains you have in that
skull of yours!
149:
Yes sir! I mean ma'am! I'll protect
this city!
152:
Well. Nobody ever said my taste in
men was impeccable. Can we just
pretend that didn't happen?
157:
Just WHAT was that?! Y-you... You've
got some explaining to do! For one,
he's FAR too young for you!
161:
A-and surely you're not implying
that there are OTHERS? What's
gotten into you?!
165:
*sigh* Even if I could understand
your flustered babbling, I wouldn't
answer.
168:
Wait... 
Hah... Hahaha... HAHA! Don't tell
me—you've been holding out for me
for over FIFTY years?!
171:
My dear Gram... You really an utter,
hopeless fool.
181:
It looks like we're out of time. A
shame—I really would have liked to
talk longer about all the rich
nuances of your stupidity.
183:
Once this battle is over, remind me
to tell you about our daughter, all
right?
191:
Oh, and we're grandparents now as
well! If you want to know more, I
guess you'd better come out of this
alive!
200:
Come to me, puppets of the
heavens! Let Nihilyana Voluntas put
you in your place!
202:
O Darkness that lurks within all
creation. O Light that reveals all
creation!
206:
Carve falsehoods upon truths! Pave
our path ever forward!
